The paper proposes a deep learning framework for fingerprint recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the security aspect of fingerprint recognition, which could be categorized under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a large-scale dataset, which could be categorized under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of visualization techniques, which could be categorized under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
